        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            
            <p>Company started in 1825 by Robert Bacon to make hats. John H. Bacon and Charles N.
                Bacon later joined the company. Twenty-five years later it began manufacturing
                all-wool sheet felt for the wallpaper trade, marble polishing and other mechanical
                uses. It also made felt wheels for polishing &amp; burnishing. The company was
                bought by Stanley &amp; Samuel McNeily in 1941. Includes 2 letterbooks, 1869-1870
                and 1873. Also includes 1979 newspaper article on history of company.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            
            <p>Contains incoming correspondence, 1869-1870, 1873, concerning both business and
                family matters. Also includes a newspaper clipping from the Winchester Star, Oct.
                25, 1979, giving a history of the company</p>
        </scopecontent>
